  "body": "Colon in a filename trips up linux tools like ssh, scp, and tar ([shockingly](http://steve-parker.org/linux/tar-colon-filename/)). As a result, writing the script to archive, copy between systems, and restore a snapshot took 3x longer than it had to. I'd propose changing the name format for snapshots to be more script-friendly\r\n\r\n(moved from https://github.com/prometheus/tsdb/issues/221)\r\n",
